EXTRACTED VALUE: Project Sylpheed is one of those games you desperately want to like, but falls short in almost every category.
Between Spider Sense and the web slinging, Spider-Man 3 offers a fairly comprehensive Spidey experience, but there's as much frustration as fun here.
The action is incredibly easy. We rarely had trouble with events, particularly the formal tennis matches.
The game is let down by a severe lack of atmosphere, repetitive missions and ships that are too weighty to control. [Issue 20, p.60]
In the end, Friend or Foe is only advised to its demographic, and even so with a lot of reservations.
